Licensing — minspec-monorepo
=============================

This repository is multi-licensed. Each package carries its own LICENSE file,
which is authoritative for that package. See DR-018 for the rationale.

| Path                        | License      | What                                            |
|-----------------------------|--------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| packages/shared             | MPL-2.0      | Core library: tier classifier + contract types  |
| packages/minspec            | MIT          | MinSpec VS Code extension (end-user app)         |
| packages/scroogellm         | MIT          | ScroogeLLM VS Code extension (end-user app)      |
| packages/extension-pack     | MIT          | MinSpec Pro extension pack                        |
| docs/, sites/ copy, whitepaper | CC-BY-4.0 | Prose/content — see LICENSE-CONTENT              |
| scripts/, root tooling      | MIT          | Dev-time monorepo tooling                         |

Why MPL-2.0 for `packages/shared` and MIT for everything else: the shared
package is the one reusable *library* and the project's core IP (the T1–T4
complexity classifier). MPL-2.0's file-level copyleft keeps modifications to
those source files open while still permitting commercial tools to depend on
it. The extensions are end-user applications with no library to protect, so
MIT removes all adoption friction. See docs/decisions/DR-018.md.

Copyright (c) 2026 AI Clarity.
